28/11/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Army Lieutenant General Sergiu Tudor Medar has been named head of the new National Intelligence Community, established in Romania earlier this month in a bid to centralise intelligence information. The National Defence Council tapped Medar at the weekend. He also will serve as a presidential adviser for defence and national security. 
In other news, Romanian authorities renewed their campaign against bird flu Sunday by culling thousands of birds and quarantining a remote village outside the Danube delta. The move came after a turkey in Scarlatesti tested positive for the virus. (Nine o'clock - 28/11/05; Reuters, AFP, AP - 27/11/05)
